                    <b>Nutritional content :</b>

                    Apples, oranges, and bananas are all nutritious fruits that contain vitamins, minerals, and fiber:
                    <br /> <br />
                    <b>Apples:</b>

                    Contain fiber, antioxidants, and phytochemicals like flavonoids and proanthocyanidins. They can help with digestion and control blood pressure, cholesterol, and blood sugar.
                    <br /> <br />
                    <b>Oranges:</b>

                    Contain vitamin C, calcium, folates, thiamine, flavanones, and naringin. They are calorie-negative and can be eaten as a snack or in fresh juice.
                    <br /> <br />
                    <b>Bananas:</b>

                    Contain soluble fiber, pectin, and resistant starch, which can help reduce appetite and increase feelings of fullness. They also contain tryptophan, which can help prevent depression, and calcium, which can help build strong bones.
