        Sugar content
        Bananas contain 15.4 grams of sugar per banana, and other fruits with high sugar content include apples, cherries, figs, pears, mangoes, and pomegranates.
        Acidity
        Apples, oranges, and strawberries are acidic, while bananas are slightly basic. A pH less than 7 is acidic, and a pH greater than 7 is basic.
        Health benefits
        Eating a range of fruits can provide the body with nutrients and antioxidants that can boost overall health. A diet high in fruits and vegetables can reduce a person's risk of developing heart disease, cancer, inflammation, and diabetes.



